##13 people were infected by bus. "New coronavirus can spread 4.5 meters under certain circumstances. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

He Niantai, reporter, thepaper.cn

At present, with the resumption of work to resume production has been pushed forward, the prevention and control of public transport epidemic has become increasingly important.

A recent study explored the possibility of Aerosol transmission in a closed environment, using a cluster of 13 people infected by public transport as a case study, the www.thepaper.cn  noted.

The study found that the COVID-19 virus is highly contagious, spreading as far as 4.5 m in an air conditioned compartment, and can float in the air for at least 30 minutes, leading to infection. Therefore, it is recommended to take public transport to do a good job of personal protection, while ensuring public transport ventilation and fresh air volume, do a good job in the car cleaning and disinfection.

One person on a bus infected eight others

The study, entitled an Epidemiological Investigation of an aggregated pneumonia epidemic spread by Aerosol in public transport, was first published on March 5 in the Journal of Applied Preventive Medicine, sponsored by the COVID-19. The authors include Luo Kaiwei, Hai Zheng and others.

A case of a suspected case of new crown pneumonia (case a) was reported on January 28,2006 in a cluster of cases caused by public transportation in Hunan Province.

The patient became ill on January 22 and was diagnosed on January 29. On the 5th and 3rd days before onset, he and his colleague, surnamed Li (confirmed case, onset on January 16) had the experience of dining and working together.

At 12 o'clock on January 22, case a (without a mask) arrived at 14 o'clock on a bus carrying case A to B, resulting in seven cases (case b-case h) and one asymptomatic infection (case I) .

January 22 at 15:40, case a (not wearing a mask) by bus, the journey of about 1 hour, resulting in the same car 2 people sick (Case K and case l) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This aggregated epidemic transmission chain map of this article pictures are from the relevant papers

On the same day, the bus of case a arrived at site B and stayed for 30 minutes (during which the vehicle was not disinfected) , then returned to site a with passengers. One passenger (case j) became ill on January 24 after boarding the bus (the seat was adjacent to the seat previously occupied by Case A. Case J had no other special travel or contact history.

The outbreak has also triggered three successive generations of cases: Case B, which is in the same car with Case A, and Case K, which is followed by one relative, case M and Case N.

Under what circumstances was this concentrated outbreak that infected 13 people?

Study showed that the case A122 noon on the 49-seat fully enclosed air-conditioned passenger bus. The bus has a baggage compartment on the first floor and a passenger compartment on the second floor. The length and width of the bus are 11.3 M and 2.5 M. The driver's seat is at the front of the upper level. There are 48 passenger seats in addition to the driver. 46 passengers are on board when the vehicle leaves the station and 2 are on the side of the road.

Case A is less than 0.5 m away from the most recent infected person (case e) in the vehicle and about 4.5 m away from the most distant infected person (case g) .

According to the investigation, case G and case a got on and off the bus from the front and back doors respectively, and there was no close contact behavior on the way. Pulling up the video on the car at the time, most of the people on the car were not wearing masks, the car was infected cases were not wearing masks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Case Athe bus and the seat of the infected person (case) from place A to place B at noon on January 22

On the afternoon of January 22, case a was on an 18-seat air-conditioned minibus with the Windows Open. It is 5.5 m long and 2.5 m wide. There are 17 seats, except for the driver. A total of 12 people on the bus, only one wearing a mask, the car was infected with 2 people did not wear a mask. The distance between case a and the farthest case (Case K) is about 4.5 m.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Case Athe afternoon of 22 January 2002, the minibus from Area B to Area C and the seating condition of the infected person (case) 

The new coronavirus has the possibility of Aerosol transmission in the closed environment

The study noted that a total of 243 close contacts were identified in the cluster outbreak, of which 10 confirmed cases and one asymptomatic infection. Close contacts of Case B of the Second Generation M and Case K of the second generation n also became ill.

In addition, 10 second-generation cases and 1 asymptomatic infected person were exposed to the bus together with the confirmed case A, no other clear history of epidemiological exposure was found. No other epidemiological history was found except for a clear history of exposure with one confirmed case in this case.

There are two important implications for the mode of transmission of COVID-19, according to the study.

One is in the air-conditioned compartment, the spread of the virus is likely to exceed the current thought of the spread of droplets distance (usually 1m) . In this investigation, case a was on a fully enclosed air-conditioned bus with a distance of about 4.5 m from the farthest infected person (case g) .

"The likely reason is that in a completely enclosed space, the flow of air is driven mainly by hot air generated by air conditioning, and the rise of hot air can transport virus-carrying droplets over long distances, far beyond the 1m distance commonly recognized, " the study said, the long-distance transmission in this outbreak also suggests the possibility of Aerosol transmission in a confined environment, said COVID-19, an epidemiologist at the University of California, San Diego. Also, in a closed environment with air conditioning, the propagation distance of the COVID-19 is greater than the commonly recognized distance of 1 ~ 2 meters.

Second, the effective survival time of the virus in the carriage is not less than 30 minutes, and the virus stock can reach the level that can cause human disease. If the case a bus stops at B for 30 minutes, a passenger (case j) will return to a bus, during which he will become infected.

The study said the outbreak has some implications for the personal protection of the public, especially those travelling on public transport.

During the epidemic period, travelers should prepare protective articles, according to the length of stay, sanitation facilities, and so on, to prepare a certain number of medical masks, hands-free disinfectant, etc. . Wear a mask when travelling on public transport such as MTR, bus or aircraft. Keep hands out of the public area and avoid touching the face before cleaning. Ventilation should be maintained and windows, including those in the driver's compartment, should be properly opened. For closed / air-conditioned compartments, the fresh air supply should be maximized to increase the number of air changes. In general, 1-2 times a day in the car cleaning disinfection, pay special attention to arrive at the terminal after disembarkation of the vehicle interior space for cleaning and disinfection 1.

According to the fifth edition of the COVID-19 issued by the General Office of the State Health Commission on February 21, the main transmission route for COVID-19 is through respiratory droplets and contact, thepaper.cn noted, in the relatively closed environment, long-term exposure to high concentrations of aerosols may result in the transmission of aerosols, and other transmission routes remain to be determined.

On March 3, the General Office and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine of the National Health Commission issued the seventh edition of the program for diagnosis and treatment of COVID-19 pneumonia, the COVID-19"has the potential to be transmitted by aerosols when exposed to high concentrations of aerosols in a relatively closed environment for long periods of time. " . Also, since COVID-19 can be separated from faeces and urine, it should be noted that faeces and urine can cause aerosol or contact transmission.

The study found that the virus could survive on smooth surfaces for hours, said Jiang Rongmeng, a member of the National Health Commission's Expert Group and chief physician of the Second Department of infection at Temple of Earth Hospital in Beijing. If the temperature and humidity are right, it may survive for several days or even up to five days.
